-- PRESS DIGEST - Bulgaria - Oct 28
-- 
-- Tue Oct 28, 2014 03:05AM EDT
-- None



SOFIA, Oct 28 (Reuters) - These are some of the main stories in Bulgarian newspapers on Tuesday. Reuters has not verified these stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.

-- Some 86 of the companies that have received loans from troubled Corporate Commercial Bank <6C9.BB> were registered at 7 addresses, a central bank report said, pointing this was one of the ways of the bank to avoid reporting huge expositions to one group. (Trud, Capital Daily, Presa, Sega, 24 Chasa) -- The interim government will tender on Tuesday in parliament its proposal for a revision in 2014 budget law, which envisions a spike of the budget deficit to 4.0 percent of gross domestic product and raising of 4.5 billion levs in new debt to prop up banks. (Presa, Capital Daily, Duma) -- The ethic Turkish MRF party said it would not support a coalition government that will include nationalist Patriotic Front. (Capital Daily, Presa, 24 Chasa)